TNS will now present a series of QuickNotes.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

2600 Magazine was recently mentioned in PC Magazine by writer John Dvorak.
The article was pro-2600 Magazine and writer John Dvorak wrote that he liked
the magazine.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

The LOD/H Technical Journal #3 is due to be released very soon if not already
released by this time.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

It is suspected that a hacker/rodent named Agent X is being SUED by Martin
Telecom (or whatever) for $1,000,000. He ran a bulletin board which had codes
posted regularly. The board, known as Hackers Heaven (312), was promptly
disconnected. Of course this isn't the first time that a hacker has been
sued. Allnet Communications Inc. has done this on several occasions and
Sprint set the record for a suit of $20,000,000 (20 Million) against a
so-called "ring" of code-sellers.

It is believed that this individual is being blamed for all losses on every
code posted on his BBS.

Note: not all of this is confirmed since this person cannot be reached.

If this is an incorrect assumption, then I apoligize to Agent X.. even
though several sources have verified this.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Phrack Magazine will most likely release Phrack Issue 17 in the next few
weeks.

